init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When people choose to listen to audiobooks, there are still advantages and disadvantages that come with the process.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: tasks, such as household chores or driving.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is well known that listeners are more distracted by outside stimuli when they are listening to a book than when they are reading the book themselves.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: as opposed to how a person reads the book itself.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I do however appreciate how audiobooks are available to me, in my interests, and can be enjoyed on my time.
